# Docker Image Layers

Every Dockerfile instruction creates one layer.

Example

```dockerfile
FROM ubuntu
RUN apt update
RUN apt install nginx
COPY index.html .
CMD ["nginx","-g","daemon off;"]
```

Layers

Layer 5 → CMD

Layer 4 → COPY

Layer 3 → RUN apt install nginx

Layer 2 → RUN apt update

Layer 1 → Ubuntu

---

# Why Docker Builds are Fast?

Docker caches layers.

If only COPY changes,

Docker rebuilds only COPY layer.

Remaining layers are reused.

