# Linux Concepts Used by Docker

## Bind Mount

Shares host files with container.

---

## Networking

Provides communication between containers and host.

Example

```
Host Port 8080
        │
Container Port 80
```

---

## System Calls

Container accesses CPU, memory and disk through Linux kernel.

Container

↓

System Call

↓

Linux Kernel

↓

Hardware

---

## Namespaces

Provide isolation.

Each container has its own

* Processes
* Network
* File system
* Hostname

---

## Control Groups (cgroups)

Limit resources.

Can limit

* CPU
* Memory
* Disk I/O

Example

```bash
docker run --memory=1g ubuntu
```

Container cannot use more than 1 GB RAM.

---

# Difference Between Dockerfile and Docker Compose

Dockerfile

* Builds one image.
* Describes how to create an image.

Docker Compose

* Runs multiple containers together.
* Defines services.
* Creates network automatically.
* Manages ports, environment variables and volumes.

